 [FILES] Accounting professionals have charted paths on how to assist companies increase their chances of survival. Photo: BUSINESS  Author of the report and Global Head of Business, ACCA, Jamie Lyon, who presented the publication, explained how organisations globally are responding to the COVID-19 crisis, and what ACCA’s recommendations are for charting a path to recovery. The report maintained that the long term financial impact of COVID-19 seemed to be growing increasingly clear, as leading indicators suggest that the global economy was entering into a deep recession, yet remained impossible to understand the true long term consequences.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .